Definition.WordDefinition:
Pregnancy \Preg"nan*cy\, n. 1. The condition of being pregnant; the state of being with young. [1913 Webster]
2. Figuratively: The quality of being heavy with important contents, issue, significance, etc.; unusual consequence or capacity; fertility. --Fuller. [1913 Webster]
pregnancy n : the state of being pregnant; the period from conception to birth when a woman carries a developing fetus in her uterus [syn: {gestation}, {maternity}]
